## Common Mistakes to Avoid

### Rule Syntax Errors

❌ **Wrong: Spaces before rules**
```
[List.Rules:MyRules]
  c           # NO SPACES!
  c$1$2$3
```

✅ **Correct: No spaces**
```
[List.Rules:MyRules]
c
c$1$2$3
```

---

❌ **Wrong: Missing section header**
```
c
c$1$2$3
```

✅ **Correct: Include section name**
```
[List.Rules:MyRules]
c
c$1$2$3
```

---

❌ **Wrong: Using wrong rule name**
```
# Defined as [List.Rules:MyRules]
john hash.txt --rules=TestRules  # Wrong name!
```

✅ **Correct: Use exact name**
```
# Defined as [List.Rules:MyRules]
john hash.txt --rules=MyRules  # Correct!
```

### File Cracking Errors

❌ **Wrong: Trying to crack ZIP directly**
```
john secure.zip --wordlist=rockyou.txt
```

✅ **Correct: Extract hash first**
```
zip2john secure.zip > hash.txt
john hash.txt --wordlist=rockyou.txt
```

---

❌ **Wrong: Using cat on binary file**
```
cat secure.zip  # Shows gibberish (PK...)
```

✅ **Correct: Extract then unzip**
```
unzip -P password secure.zip
cat extracted_file.txt
```

