## Command Reference

### Creating Rules
```bash
# Edit config
sudo nano /etc/john/john.conf

# Add at bottom
[List.Rules:RuleName]
rule1
rule2

# Save: Ctrl+O, Enter
# Exit: Ctrl+X
```

### Using Rules
```bash
# Basic usage
john hash.txt --wordlist=words.txt --rules=RuleName

# Preview rules (no cracking)
john --wordlist=words.txt --rules=RuleName --stdout

# With specific format
john --format=nt hash.txt --wordlist=words.txt --rules=RuleName
```

### File Cracking
```bash
# ZIP
zip2john file.zip > hash.txt
john hash.txt --wordlist=rockyou.txt
unzip -P password file.zip

# RAR
rar2john file.rar > hash.txt
john hash.txt --wordlist=rockyou.txt
unrar x -ppassword file.rar

# SSH Key
ssh2john id_rsa > hash.txt
john hash.txt --wordlist=rockyou.txt
ssh -i id_rsa user@server

# PDF
pdf2john file.pdf > hash.txt
john hash.txt --wordlist=rockyou.txt

# Office
office2john file.docx > hash.txt
john hash.txt --wordlist=rockyou.txt
```

### Viewing Results
```bash
# Show cracked passwords
john --show hash.txt

# Show with specific format
john --show --format=nt hash.txt

# Check cracking progress
john --status

# Resume interrupted session
john --restore
```

