## Key Takeaways

### Custom Rules

✅ Rules transform wordlist entries into targeted variations  
✅ Based on human password psychology and patterns  
✅ Dramatically increase crack success rate  
✅ Essential for corporate/targeted pentests  
✅ Require OSINT for maximum effectiveness  

### Rule Syntax

✅ `c` = Capitalize, `u` = Uppercase, `l` = Lowercase  
✅ `$X` = Append X, `^X` = Prepend X  
✅ `sXY` = Replace X with Y (sa@ = a→@)  
✅ Combine operations: `csa@so0$1$2$3$!`  
✅ Test with `--stdout` before cracking  

### File Cracking

✅ Always extract hash first with appropriate tool (*2john)  
✅ Crack hash file, not original file  
✅ Use --show to view results  
✅ Works for: ZIP, RAR, PDF, Office, SSH, KeePass, etc.  
✅ Essential for forensics and incident response  

### Real-World Application

✅ OSINT → Custom wordlist → Custom rules → Targeted attack  
✅ 90% intelligence gathering, 10% technical execution  
✅ Understanding user behavior > brute force  
✅ Document everything for professional reporting  
✅ Works for both offensive and defensive security  

